==English==
===Noun===
'''rhinoceroses'''

#A plural of '''[[rhinoceros]]'''.

====Usage notes====
*In natural history, the plural ''rhinoceros'' is often used, in the same way that the singular of the names of many wild animals is often used in natural history as the plural (compare "gazelle", "elephant", etc).
*The supposed plural ''rhinoceri'' does not exist in English.
*The etymologically correct plural of rhinoceros is [[rhinocerotes]]; however, this form is archaic.